children.subject: You might want to consider taking 61A instead if Data8 is unable to accomodate you off the waitlist. You’ll develop stronger coding fundamentals (as well as a better working knowledge of Python) from 61A than Data8. At least that was my impression  from taking both of those classes.

COMPSCI//DATA C8

Hi everyone,

I am wondering if there will be an expansion of DATA 8//COMPSCI 8 during Phase two. I am a new transfer student majoring in economics, and I would like to take data 8 so that I can learn more about Python. However, my waitlist postion is pretty low, (around 150), so I am not sure whether or not it is actually likely for me to get in.

history.content:
Porting answer in DS Piazza by instructor David Wagner:

"

Good question!  I don't know.  I don't have a magic ball.  In the past we've managed to accommodate nearly all students who wanted to take the course and that was my hope for this fall as well, but it looks like this fall we might be experiencing growth that has exceeded even our most generous projections.  We already bumped up the cap significantly earlier this summer and I wasn't expecting us to blow through even that cap, so at this point all I can do is say that I don't know what to expect.

 

I guess we'll have to see what happens with drops and how many people drop the course in the first few weeks.

 

My sympathies about the situation.  I'd love to be able to meet student demand but I don't know whether that will be possible.

"
Are there any plans to expand Data 8 this upcoming semester to accommodate waitlisted students? I'm a sophomore and hope to get into the class.
